{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So I was born"},{"time":2000,"text":"on the last day"},{"time":4000,"text":"of the last year of the '70s."},{"time":8000,"text":"I was raised on \"Free to be you and me\" --"},{"time":11000,"text":"(cheering)"},{"time":13000,"text":"hip-hop --"},{"time":15000,"text":"not as many woohoos for hip-hop in the house."},{"time":17000,"text":"Thank you. Thank you for hip-hop --"},{"time":20000,"text":"and Anita Hill."},{"time":22000,"text":"(Cheering)"},{"time":25000,"text":"My parents were radicals --"},{"time":28000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":30000,"text":"who became,"},{"time":32000,"text":"well, grown-ups."},{"time":35000,"text":"My dad facetiously says,"},{"time":37000,"text":"\"We wanted to save the world,"},{"time":39000,"text":"and instead we just got rich.\""},{"time":43000,"text":"We actually just got \"middle class\""},{"time":45000,"text":"in Colorado Springs, Colorado,"},{"time":47000,"text":"but you get the picture."},{"time":49000,"text":"I was raised with a very heavy sense"},{"time":51000,"text":"of unfinished legacy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53000,"text":"At this ripe old age of 30,"},{"time":56000,"text":"I've been thinking a lot about what it means to grow up"},{"time":59000,"text":"in this horrible, beautiful time,"},{"time":62000,"text":"and I've decided, for me,"},{"time":64000,"text":"it's been a real journey and paradox."},{"time":67000,"text":"The first paradox"},{"time":69000,"text":"is that growing up is about rejecting the past"},{"time":71000,"text":"and then promptly reclaiming it."},{"time":73000,"text":"Feminism was the water I grew up in."},{"time":76000,"text":"When I was just a little girl,"},{"time":78000,"text":"my mom started what is now"},{"time":80000,"text":"the longest-running women's film festival in the world."},{"time":83000,"text":"So while other kids were watching sitcoms and cartoons,"},{"time":86000,"text":"I was watching very esoteric documentaries"},{"time":89000,"text":"made by and about women."},{"time":91000,"text":"You can see how this had an influence."},{"time":93000,"text":"But she was not the only feminist in the house."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96000,"text":"My dad actually resigned"},{"time":98000,"text":"from the male-only business club in my hometown"},{"time":101000,"text":"because he said he would never be part of an organization"},{"time":104000,"text":"that would one day welcome his son, but not his daughter."},{"time":107000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":112000,"text":"He's actually here today."},{"time":114000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":119000,"text":"The trick here"},{"time":121000,"text":"is my brother would become an experimental poet,"},{"time":123000,"text":"not a businessman,"},{"time":125000,"text":"but the intention was really good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":129000,"text":"In any case, I didn't readily claim the feminist label,"},{"time":131000,"text":"even though it was all around me,"},{"time":133000,"text":"because I associated it with my mom's women's groups,"},{"time":135000,"text":"her swishy skirts and her shoulder pads --"},{"time":138000,"text":"none of which had much cachet"},{"time":140000,"text":"in the hallways of Palmer High School"},{"time":142000,"text":"where I was trying to be cool at the time."},{"time":144000,"text":"But I suspected there was something really important"},{"time":146000,"text":"about this whole feminism thing,"},{"time":148000,"text":"so I started covertly tiptoeing into my mom's bookshelves"},{"time":152000,"text":"and picking books off and reading them --"},{"time":155000,"text":"never, of course, admitting that I was doing so."},{"time":157000,"text":"I didn't actually claim the feminist label"},{"time":160000,"text":"until I went to Barnard College"},{"time":162000,"text":"and I heard Amy Richards and Jennifer Baumgardner speak for the first time."},{"time":166000,"text":"They were the co-authors of a book called \"Manifesta.\""},{"time":169000,"text":"So what very profound epiphany, you might ask,"},{"time":172000,"text":"was responsible for my feminist click moment?"},{"time":175000,"text":"Fishnet stockings."},{"time":177000,"text":"Jennifer Baumgardner was wearing them."},{"time":179000,"text":"I thought they were really hot."},{"time":181000,"text":"I decided, okay, I can claim the feminist label."},{"time":183000,"text":"Now I tell you this --"},{"time":186000,"text":"I tell you this at the risk of embarrassing myself,"},{"time":189000,"text":"because I think part of the work of feminism"},{"time":191000,"text":"is to admit that aesthetics, that beauty,"},{"time":193000,"text":"that fun do matter."},{"time":195000,"text":"There are lots of very modern political movements"},{"time":198000,"text":"that have caught fire in no small part"},{"time":200000,"text":"because of cultural hipness."},{"time":202000,"text":"Anyone heard of these two guys as an example?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":205000,"text":"So my feminism is very indebted to my mom's,"},{"time":208000,"text":"but it looks very different."},{"time":210000,"text":"My mom says, \"patriarchy.\""},{"time":212000,"text":"I say, \"intersectionality.\""},{"time":214000,"text":"So race, class, gender, ability,"},{"time":217000,"text":"all of these things go into our experiences"},{"time":219000,"text":"of what it means to be a woman."},{"time":221000,"text":"Pay equity? Yes. Absolutely a feminist issue."},{"time":223000,"text":"But for me, so is immigration. (Applause)"},{"time":226000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":229000,"text":"My mom says, \"Protest march.\""},{"time":231000,"text":"I say, \"Online organizing.\""},{"time":234000,"text":"I co-edit, along with a collective"},{"time":236000,"text":"of other super-smart, amazing women,"},{"time":238000,"text":"a site called Feministing.com."},{"time":241000,"text":"We are the most widely read feminist publication ever,"},{"time":246000,"text":"and I tell you this"},{"time":248000,"text":"because I think it's really important to see"},{"time":250000,"text":"that there's a continuum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252000,"text":"Feminist blogging is basically the 21st century version"},{"time":255000,"text":"of consciousness raising."},{"time":257000,"text":"But we also have a straightforward political impact."},{"time":260000,"text":"Feministing has been able"},{"time":262000,"text":"to get merchandise pulled off the shelves of Walmart."},{"time":264000,"text":"We got a misogynist administrator sending us hate-mail"},{"time":267000,"text":"fired from a Big Ten school."},{"time":269000,"text":"And one of our biggest successes"},{"time":272000,"text":"is we get mail from teenage girls in the middle of Iowa"},{"time":275000,"text":"who say, \"I Googled Jessica Simpson and stumbled on your site."},{"time":278000,"text":"I realized feminism wasn't about man-hating and Birkenstocks.\""},{"time":281000,"text":"So we're able to pull in the next generation"},{"time":284000,"text":"in a totally new way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286000,"text":"My mom says, \"Gloria Steinem.\""},{"time":289000,"text":"I say, \"Samhita Mukhopadhyay,"},{"time":291000,"text":"Miriam Perez, Ann Friedman,"},{"time":293000,"text":"Jessica Valenti, Vanessa Valenti,"},{"time":295000,"text":"and on and on and on and on.\""},{"time":297000,"text":"We don't want one hero."},{"time":299000,"text":"We don't want one icon."},{"time":301000,"text":"We don't want one face."},{"time":303000,"text":"We are thousands of women and men across this country"},{"time":306000,"text":"doing online writing, community organizing,"},{"time":309000,"text":"changing institutions from the inside out --"},{"time":312000,"text":"all continuing the incredible work"},{"time":314000,"text":"that our mothers and grandmothers started."},{"time":318000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":322000,"text":"Which brings me to the second paradox:"},{"time":324000,"text":"sobering up about our smallness"},{"time":326000,"text":"and maintaining faith in our greatness"},{"time":328000,"text":"all at once."},{"time":330000,"text":"Many in my generation --"},{"time":332000,"text":"because of well-intentioned parenting and self-esteem education --"},{"time":335000,"text":"were socialized to believe"},{"time":337000,"text":"that we were special little snowflakes --"},{"time":339000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":341000,"text":"who were going to go out and save the world."},{"time":344000,"text":"These are three words many of us were raised with."},{"time":347000,"text":"We walk across graduation stages,"},{"time":349000,"text":"high on our overblown expectations,"},{"time":351000,"text":"and when we float back down to earth,"},{"time":353000,"text":"we realize we don't know what the heck it means"},{"time":355000,"text":"to actually save the world anyway."},{"time":358000,"text":"The mainstream media often paints my generation"},{"time":361000,"text":"as apathetic,"},{"time":363000,"text":"and I think it's much more accurate"},{"time":365000,"text":"to say we are deeply overwhelmed."},{"time":367000,"text":"And there's a lot to be overwhelmed about, to be fair --"},{"time":369000,"text":"an environmental crisis,"},{"time":371000,"text":"wealth disparity in this country"},{"time":373000,"text":"unlike we've seen since 1928,"},{"time":375000,"text":"and globally,"},{"time":377000,"text":"a totally immoral and ongoing wealth disparity."},{"time":380000,"text":"Xenophobia's on the rise. The trafficking of women and girls."},{"time":383000,"text":"It's enough to make you feel very overwhelmed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386000,"text":"I experienced this firsthand myself"},{"time":388000,"text":"when I graduated from Barnard College in 2002."},{"time":391000,"text":"I was fired up; I was ready to make a difference."},{"time":393000,"text":"I went out and I worked at a non-profit,"},{"time":395000,"text":"I went to grad school, I phone-banked,"},{"time":398000,"text":"I protested, I volunteered,"},{"time":401000,"text":"and none of it seemed to matter."},{"time":405000,"text":"And on a particularly dark night"},{"time":407000,"text":"of December of 2004,"},{"time":409000,"text":"I sat down with my family,"},{"time":411000,"text":"and I said that I had become very disillusioned."},{"time":415000,"text":"I admitted that I'd actually had a fantasy -- kind of a dark fantasy --"},{"time":418000,"text":"of writing a letter"},{"time":420000,"text":"about everything that was wrong with the world"},{"time":422000,"text":"and then lighting myself on fire"},{"time":424000,"text":"on the White House steps."},{"time":427000,"text":"My mom"},{"time":429000,"text":"took a drink of her signature Sea Breeze,"},{"time":433000,"text":"her eyes really welled with tears,"},{"time":436000,"text":"and she looked right at me and she said,"},{"time":439000,"text":"\"I will not stand"},{"time":441000,"text":"for your desperation.\""},{"time":443000,"text":"She said, \"You are smarter, more creative"},{"time":446000,"text":"and more resilient than that.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"Which brings me to my third paradox."},{"time":452000,"text":"Growing up is about aiming to succeed wildly"},{"time":454000,"text":"and being fulfilled by failing really well."},{"time":457000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":459000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":461000,"text":"There's a writer I've been deeply influenced by, Parker Palmer,"},{"time":464000,"text":"and he writes that many of us are often whiplashed"},{"time":466000,"text":"\"between arrogant overestimation of ourselves"},{"time":469000,"text":"and a servile underestimation of ourselves.\""},{"time":472000,"text":"You may have guessed by now,"},{"time":474000,"text":"I did not light myself on fire."},{"time":476000,"text":"I did what I know to do in desperation, which is write."},{"time":479000,"text":"I wrote the book I needed to read."},{"time":482000,"text":"I wrote a book about eight incredible people"},{"time":484000,"text":"all over this country"},{"time":486000,"text":"doing social justice work."},{"time":488000,"text":"I wrote about Nia Martin-Robinson,"},{"time":490000,"text":"the daughter of Detroit and two civil rights activists,"},{"time":492000,"text":"who's dedicating her life"},{"time":494000,"text":"to environmental justice."},{"time":496000,"text":"I wrote about Emily Apt"},{"time":498000,"text":"who initially became a caseworker in the welfare system"},{"time":500000,"text":"because she decided that was the most noble thing she could do,"},{"time":503000,"text":"but quickly learned, not only did she not like it,"},{"time":505000,"text":"but she wasn't really good at it."},{"time":507000,"text":"Instead, what she really wanted to do was make films."},{"time":509000,"text":"So she made a film about the welfare system"},{"time":511000,"text":"and had a huge impact."},{"time":513000,"text":"I wrote about Maricela Guzman, the daughter of Mexican immigrants,"},{"time":516000,"text":"who joined the military so she could afford college."},{"time":520000,"text":"She was actually sexually assaulted in boot camp"},{"time":522000,"text":"and went on to co-organize a group"},{"time":524000,"text":"called the Service Women's Action Network."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527000,"text":"What I learned from these people and others"},{"time":529000,"text":"was that I couldn't judge them"},{"time":531000,"text":"based on their failure to meet their very lofty goals."},{"time":534000,"text":"Many of them are working in deeply intractable systems --"},{"time":537000,"text":"the military, congress,"},{"time":539000,"text":"the education system, etc."},{"time":541000,"text":"But what they managed to do within those systems"},{"time":543000,"text":"was be a humanizing force."},{"time":546000,"text":"And at the end of the day,"},{"time":548000,"text":"what could possibly be more important than that?"},{"time":550000,"text":"Cornel West says, \"Of course it's a failure."},{"time":552000,"text":"But how good a failure is it?\""},{"time":555000,"text":"This isn't to say we give up our wildest, biggest dreams."},{"time":558000,"text":"It's to say we operate on two levels."},{"time":560000,"text":"On one,"},{"time":562000,"text":"we really go after changing these broken systems"},{"time":564000,"text":"of which we find ourselves a part."},{"time":566000,"text":"But on the other, we root our self-esteem"},{"time":568000,"text":"in the daily acts of trying to make one person's day"},{"time":571000,"text":"more kind, more just, etc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574000,"text":"So when I was a little girl,"},{"time":576000,"text":"I had a couple of very strange habits."},{"time":578000,"text":"One of them was"},{"time":580000,"text":"I used to lie on the kitchen floor of my childhood home,"},{"time":582000,"text":"and I would suck the thumb of my left hand"},{"time":584000,"text":"and hold my mom's cold toes with my right hand."},{"time":587000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":589000,"text":"I was listening to her talk on the phone, which she did a lot."},{"time":592000,"text":"She was talking about board meetings,"},{"time":595000,"text":"she was founding peace organizations,"},{"time":597000,"text":"she was coordinating carpools, she was consoling friends --"},{"time":600000,"text":"all these daily acts of care and creativity."},{"time":603000,"text":"And surely, at three and four years old,"},{"time":605000,"text":"I was listening to the soothing sound of her voice,"},{"time":608000,"text":"but I think I was also getting my first lesson in activist work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"The activists I interviewed"},{"time":613000,"text":"had nothing in common, literally, except for one thing,"},{"time":616000,"text":"which was that they all cited their mothers"},{"time":618000,"text":"as their most looming and important"},{"time":620000,"text":"activist influences."},{"time":622000,"text":"So often, particularly at a young age,"},{"time":624000,"text":"we look far afield"},{"time":627000,"text":"for our models of the meaningful life,"},{"time":629000,"text":"and sometimes they're in our own kitchens,"},{"time":632000,"text":"talking on the phone, making us dinner,"},{"time":634000,"text":"doing all that keeps the world going around and around."},{"time":638000,"text":"My mom and so many women like her"},{"time":640000,"text":"have taught me that life is not about glory,"},{"time":643000,"text":"or certainty, or security even."},{"time":646000,"text":"It's about embracing the paradox."},{"time":648000,"text":"It's about acting in the face of overwhelm."},{"time":651000,"text":"And it's about loving people really well."},{"time":654000,"text":"And at the end of the day,"},{"time":656000,"text":"these things make for a lifetime"},{"time":659000,"text":"of challenge and reward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}